OL,3,COfcom considering 'statutory sanction'
OL,4,Cagainst GB News over Sunak programme
OL,6,FThe regulator highlighted several
OL,7,Fexamples where the broadcaster failed
OL,8,Fto remain impartial, including
OL,9,Faudience members not being able to
OL,10,Fchallenge Mr Sunak's responses to
OL,11,Ftheir questions, nor the presenter of
OL,12,Fthe show doing it to any "meaningful
OL,13,Fextent".
OL,15,FOfcom also said the prime minister
OL,16,Fcriticised aspects of the Labour
OL,17,FParty's policies and performance.
OL,19,FWhile this is allowed, GB News is
OL,20,Fresponsible for ensuring due
OL,21,Fimpartiality is preserved.
