OL,3,COfcom considering 'statutory sanction'
OL,4,Cagainst GB News over Sunak programme
OL,6,F"Neither the Labour Party's views or
OL,7,Fpositions on those issues, or any
OL,8,Fother significant views on those
OL,9,Fissues were included in the
OL,10,Fprogramme," Ofcom concluded.
OL,12,FIn a statement, GB News said: "Ofcom's
OL,13,Ffinding against GB News today is an
OL,14,Falarming development in its attempt to
OL,15,Fsilence us by standing in the way of a
OL,16,Fforum that allows the public to
OL,17,Fquestion politicians directly.
