OL,3,COfcom considering 'statutory sanction'
OL,4,Cagainst GB News over Sunak programme
OL,6,F"The regulator's threat to punish a
OL,7,Fnews organisation with sanctions for
OL,8,Fenabling people to challenge their own
OL,9,Fprime minister strikes at the heart of
OL,10,Fdemocracy at a time when it could not
OL,11,Fbe more vital."
OL,13,FGB News also called itself the
OL,14,F"people's channel" and the
OL,15,F"independently selected group of
OL,16,Fundecided voters" questioned Mr Sunak
OL,17,F"robustly, intelligently, and freely".
